    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-04-09T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-04-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="1723"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1723">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 419.11D29/51.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Price</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Panama</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-04-09">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 9, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Answering your April 7, at hand on my return from the trip to interior with
                    officials of Panama. I have not yet succeeded in communicating with Minister for
                    Foreign Affairs. It is doubtful whether it can be done before Monday on account
                    of Holy Week. I have been insistent and persistent in these matters. Minister
                    for Foreign Affairs just before trip above mentioned assured me progress in the
                    matter was real.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Price</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
